ass=m><span class=title> Helfyre's Reborn</span><hr size=1> The dark lord sat upon his throne in darkness,the eternal flames of damnation nothing but glowing embers.His followers looked up at the throne fearfully, the master had not moved, it seemed as if the gods had beaten him,that his imprisonment was permanent. The flames in his eyes had died leaving them the color of cold ash. He looked to be dead. <br>
<br>
In the dark silence, his followers waited, hoping to see a sign that their lord and master still lived. But none came. <br>
<br>
Suddenly the silence was broken, a voice pure and powerful rang throughout the darkness. Demanding the gods release the dark Prince. Other voices joined in, their collective strength breaking through the barrier preventing the dark Prince's return. His followers looked again at the throne still the fires sat dormant, still their lords eyes looked dead, he did not move. The Voices continued to echo through the darkness and suddenly one raised above the other's a menacing growl, filled with anger, a roar that shook the barrier on it's foundations. Only an Ogre could bellow like that. More bellows of anger followed as more voices joined in. <br>
<br>
Finally the dark Prince moved nothing more than a quirk of his lips flashing into an evil grin, but his minions saw it and their hopes began to rise. Through the echoing darkness the first voice rose up again louder than the rest, the sheer power of it staggering to the minions. Where his minions cowered the dark Prince grinned.<br>
<br>
&quot;Ahhh Synnovea even here in my prison your voice gives me strength.&quot; With those words the fires in his eyes ignited a raging conflagration that caused all who saw it to step away. He stood the Fires of Hell rising with him the heat blistering the flesh of the damned. Higher the flames rose, an intense inferno unlike any other ever known, even in this dark realm. With a cackle of glee, the dark Prince raised his hands the barrier shattering from the assault placed upon it from both sides. The fires of hell spilled forth across Norrath, &quot;Come my friends, my family, let us spread chaos and terror across the lands once again. The Prince of Hell has returned.&quot;<br>
<br>
Xavar Helfyre,The Prince of Hell<br>
